<paragraph id="3B21A7089957B8C4D96707CC4E5EADBE" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Habitat</paragraph>
<paragraph id="067AD8E9163E8D0EAC27E4CF7439B46A" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">
<taxonomicName id="79CA49F9E7C467D1315F6D8A75334ABD" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1833" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphelocheirus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7615084D5D8B35E0830A629C41EBBE7A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Aphelocheirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species Westwood, 1883 thrives in rather large, fast flowing rivers (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3D50FBE11A08F1CE53529676DBDF4E7F" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F5978773" captionText="Figure 1. Sampling sites at northern Mindoro (Baco, Puerto Galera). A. the first author sampling at site 396; B. Tagbinai Malaki River (305); C. Tukunan River at &quot; Hidden Paradise &quot; (303); D. lower Dulangan River (356)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e56883.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/434061" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">1</figureCitation>
D; Fig. 
<figureCitation id="43622D107488D4747B3B0CCBEB18544A" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F5978778" captionText="Figure 2. Sampling sites at the Baroc River basin (Roxas, southern Mindoro). A. lower Baroc River (BR 3); B. Hinundungan River from Hinagdanan Falls (HR 2); C. upper Taugad Daka River (TDR 4); D. small tributary of the Taugad River (TUC)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e56883.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/434062" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">2</figureCitation>
A and B) with substrates consisting of a mixture of gravel and sand. The species is a typical benthic bottom dweller.
</paragraph>
